programme.title: Live One-Day International Cricket
programme.sub-title: England v West Indies: Second ODI.
programme.desc: England v West Indies. Coverage of the second contest in the five-match series, staged at Trent Bridge. The visitors came out on top when these sides last met in an ODI on this ground back in July 2007. A knock of 82 from 126 balls by Chris Gayle, along with another 82 from Runako Morton, helped the Windies set a total of 289/5. Only Owais Shah passed 50 in England's run chase, and they were bowled out for 196(n)
